WEBVTT

00:58.183 --> 00:59.516
JACK, STOP IT!
JACK!

00:59.684 --> 01:00.976
JACK, GO AWAY!
[DOG BARKING]

01:01.144 --> 01:03.228
[HORSE WHINNIES]

01:05.190 --> 01:08.317
AAH!

01:08.485 --> 01:09.651
DOCTOR?

01:09.819 --> 01:11.278
YES?

01:11.446 --> 01:13.197
AM I REALLY
VERY SICK?

01:13.364 --> 01:15.282
YES, YOU ARE,
MARY.

01:15.450 --> 01:17.659
DO I HAVE TO HAVE
AN OPERATION?

01:17.827 --> 01:20.037
YES, MARY.

01:34.928 --> 01:37.221
HOW'S
SHE DOING?

01:37.388 --> 01:38.555
HER PULSE
IS STEADY.

01:38.723 --> 01:40.599
GOOD.

01:41.851 --> 01:43.894
GIVE HER
A LITTLE MORE.

01:48.817 --> 01:51.151
THIS IS GOING TO
TAKE A WHILE.

01:56.741 --> 01:58.242
MARY.
WHERE IS SHE?

01:58.409 --> 02:00.244
DIDN'T THEY
TELL YOU
AT THE DESK?

02:00.411 --> 02:02.621
NO ONE TOLD US
ANYTHING.
WHERE'S MARY?

02:02.789 --> 02:04.373
WHERE'S DR. MAYES?

02:04.541 --> 02:08.460
HE'S IN HIS SURGERY.
HE'S WAITING
FOR YOU THERE.

02:13.508 --> 02:15.634
[DOOR KNOCKS]

02:22.892 --> 02:25.018
DOCTOR,
WHAT HAPPENED?

02:26.312 --> 02:28.188
MARY'S FEVER
WENT BACK UP.

02:28.356 --> 02:30.065
SHE WENT INTO
CONVULSIONS.

02:30.233 --> 02:31.275
CONVULSIONS?

02:31.442 --> 02:33.152
WE'RE GOING TO
HAVE TO OPERATE
AGAIN,

02:33.319 --> 02:35.237
AND REMOVE
THE DISEASED
TISSUE.

02:35.405 --> 02:38.031
THIS WOULD HARDLY
COVER HER BILL.

02:39.075 --> 02:41.243
I KNOW THAT,
MR. BENSON.
THAT'S...

02:41.411 --> 02:43.704
THAT'S WHY
I'M GIVING YOU
MY PERSONAL NOTE.

02:43.872 --> 02:46.540
I'M GOING TO GO HOME
AND SELL MY FARM,

02:46.708 --> 02:47.875
AND I'LL PAY
THAT BILL.

02:48.042 --> 02:49.418
I'VE TOLD YOU
BEFORE,

02:49.586 --> 02:52.921
IT IS NOT THE POLICY
OF THIS INSTITUTION
TO EXTEND CREDIT.

02:53.089 --> 02:54.256
I'M NOT TALKING
ABOUT CREDIT,

02:54.424 --> 02:55.924
I'M TALKING ABOUT
MY DAUGHTER'S LIFE.

02:56.092 --> 02:57.634
I WISH
I COULD HELP.

02:57.802 --> 02:59.970
LOOK, MR. HANSON,
I'M NOT LOOKING TO MAKE
A PROFIT WITH THE PLACE.

03:00.138 --> 03:01.889
I'LL SELL YOU
THE LAND,
THE HOUSE, THE BARN,

03:02.056 --> 03:05.017
EVEN MY EQUIPMENT,
MY TOOLS, FOR ANY MONEY
YOU CAN GIVE ME.

03:05.185 --> 03:08.145
I CAN'T BUY
YOUR FARM,
CHARLES.

03:08.313 --> 03:10.439
WHERE YOU GOING?

03:10.607 --> 03:11.773
GOING WITH YOU.

03:11.941 --> 03:14.818
WE TALKED IT OVER.
IT'S WHAT
WE BOTH WANT.

03:14.986 --> 03:18.155
FIGURED THE MONEY'D BE
COMING IN TWICE AS FAST
WITH BOTH OF US WORKING.

03:18.323 --> 03:20.991
IT'LL BE OUR GIFT
TO MARY.

03:21.159 --> 03:22.826
AIN'T NO WAY
YOU CAN SAY NO,
SO DON'T.

03:22.994 --> 03:24.286
I PUT A LUNCH
IN ISAIAH'S PACK.

03:24.454 --> 03:26.747
IT'S ENOUGH
FOR BOTH OF YOU.

03:26.915 --> 03:28.749
THANK YOU.

03:28.917 --> 03:31.335
WELL, YOU BEST SAY
YOUR GOOD-BYES.
TIME WE WAS GOING.

03:31.502 --> 03:33.337
HELP YOUR
MAMA, NOW.

03:33.504 --> 03:34.671
BYE, DARLING.

03:34.839 --> 03:35.964
TAKE CARE.

03:36.132 --> 03:39.259
YOU BE GOOD
AND YOU MIND YOUR
SISTER, ALL RIGHT?

03:58.446 --> 04:00.614
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

04:41.823 --> 04:44.157
COME ON.
COME ON, THE SIGN
SAYS WHAT IT MEANS.

04:44.325 --> 04:47.536
Charles: AND WHAT ABOUT
THE POSTER I GOT IN
THE DEPOT IN ROCHESTER?

04:47.704 --> 04:49.621
WELL,
THIS IS 4 OR 5
MONTHS OLD,

04:49.789 --> 04:52.082
PROBABLY BECAUSE
SOME IDIOT FORGOT
TO TAKE IT DOWN.

04:52.250 --> 04:54.251
WELL, WE CAME
A LOT OF MILES
BECAUSE OF THAT.

04:54.419 --> 04:57.587
HEY, THAT'S YOUR IDEA.
NOBODY ASKED YOU
TO COME HERE.

04:57.755 --> 04:59.256
ALL RIGHT, THEN
AT LEAST GIVE US
A CHANCE.

04:59.424 --> 05:02.259
GIVE US A CHANCE
TO EARN BACK THE MONEY
IT COST US TO GET HERE.

05:02.427 --> 05:06.096
LOOK, I'M SORRY,
BUT I CAN'T HELP YOU.

05:06.264 --> 05:07.931
LOOK, I'M JUST
ASKING YOU
FOR A CHANCE.

05:08.099 --> 05:09.391
Isaiah:
LET GO OF HIM, CHARLES.
COME ON.

05:09.559 --> 05:11.101
I'M TELLING YOU
FOR THE LAST TIME.

05:11.269 --> 05:15.981
I TOLD YOU ONCE,
AND I'LL TELL YOU AGAIN:
WE AIN'T HIRING!

05:16.149 --> 05:17.691
Man: NOW, I'VE GOT
TO SAY THIS
10 TIMES A WEEK,

05:17.859 --> 05:20.986
AND I DON'T LIKE IT
ANY MORE THAN YOU DO.

05:21.154 --> 05:24.990
COME A LONG WAY
FOR NOTHING.

05:25.158 --> 05:28.493
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.
I'VE BEEN THERE MYSELF.

05:29.787 --> 05:31.288
HEY, LOOK, ALL RIGHT,
YOU'RE NOT HIRING.

05:31.456 --> 05:35.167
YOU KNOW ANY PLACE,
ANY KIND OF WORK WE CAN
GET AROUND HERE?

05:36.836 --> 05:38.587
[SIGHS]

05:38.755 --> 05:41.423
YEAH, THAT WAY,
ABOUT 10 MILES.

05:41.591 --> 05:43.342
BUT NO GUARANTEE.

05:43.509 --> 05:44.843
THEY'RE BUILDING
A TUNNEL UP THERE,

05:45.011 --> 05:46.303
AND THEY MIGHT
NEED SOME MEN.

05:46.471 --> 05:48.764
OR THEY MIGHT NOT.

05:50.808 --> 05:52.768
Man: ALL RIGHT,
BACK TO WORK.

05:52.935 --> 05:54.186
MOVE IT OUT.

05:54.354 --> 05:56.229
WELL...

05:56.397 --> 05:58.940
WHAT'S ANOTHER
10 MILES?

06:00.151 --> 06:01.485
COME ON.

06:16.834 --> 06:21.171
MRS. INGALLS?
MR. BENSON WOULD LIKE
TO SEE YOU, PLEASE.

06:21.339 --> 06:26.051
OH, OF COURSE.

06:26.219 --> 06:28.887
I'LL BE BACK.

06:29.055 --> 06:31.431
- THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

06:35.603 --> 06:36.728
[DOOR KNOCKS]

06:36.896 --> 06:38.980
COME IN.

06:40.525 --> 06:42.734
MR. BENSON.

06:43.861 --> 06:46.405
YOU WANTED TO
SPEAK TO ME?

06:46.572 --> 06:49.950
MRS. INGALLS,
I STILL HAVE NOT HEARD
FROM YOUR HUSBAND.

06:50.118 --> 06:52.536
YOU WILL,
MR. BENSON.

06:52.703 --> 06:55.330
YOU WILL.

06:55.498 --> 06:58.708
TIME IS RUNNING OUT,
AND THE BILLS
ARE MOUNTING.

06:58.876 --> 07:00.877
THERE'S THE EXTRA
MEDICATION

07:01.045 --> 07:03.380
AND THE ADDITIONAL
NURSING.

07:03.548 --> 07:07.092
BUT I'VE BEEN WITH MARY
ALMOST EVERY MINUTE.

07:07.260 --> 07:09.052
MRS. INGALLS,
NO MATTER HOW MUCH TIME

07:09.220 --> 07:10.429
YOU SPEND WITH
YOUR DAUGHTER,

07:10.596 --> 07:12.889
OUR NURSES
ARE RESPONSIBLE
FOR HER CARE,

07:13.057 --> 07:15.809
AND THEY MUST BE PAID
FOR THEIR WORK.

07:15.977 --> 07:19.396
MR. INGALLS
GAVE YOU HIS WORD

07:19.564 --> 07:20.897
AND HIS NOTE,

07:21.065 --> 07:22.482
AND THE MONEY
WILL CERTAINLY BE HERE

07:22.650 --> 07:25.193
AS SOON AS HE CAN
ARRANGE IT.

07:25.361 --> 07:28.029
GOOD DAY,
MR. BENSON.

07:45.298 --> 07:47.174
[DOOR CLOSES]

07:58.769 --> 08:01.271
MARY IS SLEEPING
BEAUTIFULLY.

08:09.030 --> 08:11.448
YOU'VE BEEN HERE
SUCH A LONG TIME,
MRS. INGALLS.

08:11.616 --> 08:14.075
DON'T YOU THINK
YOU SHOULD GET
SOME REST?

08:15.620 --> 08:18.371
I NEED MORE
THAN REST.

08:20.041 --> 08:21.291
I NEED A JOB.

08:21.459 --> 08:22.959
OH...

08:23.127 --> 08:24.753
TCH.

08:25.755 --> 08:27.756
IF THERE WAS
SOMETHING
AROUND HERE,

08:27.924 --> 08:30.091
SO I COULD BE
CLOSE TO MARY...

08:30.259 --> 08:32.093
I KNOW.

08:32.261 --> 08:36.097
I MEAN, I KNOW
I CAN'T QUALIFY
AS A NURSE, BUT...

08:36.265 --> 08:38.350
ANYTHING ELSE.

08:38.518 --> 08:40.727
ANYTHING AT ALL.

08:40.895 --> 08:43.730
WELL, THEY ALWAYS
NEED SOMEONE
IN THE LAUNDRY.

08:43.898 --> 08:46.983
IT'S NOT MUCH,
BUT YOU COULD START
RIGHT AWAY.

08:47.151 --> 08:48.360
THAT'LL DO
JUST FINE.

08:48.528 --> 08:51.571
WELL, FINE.
NOW COME ON AND GET
SOME REST NOW.

08:51.739 --> 08:53.490
COME ON.
I'LL SIT
WITH MARY.

09:02.166 --> 09:05.502
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

09:39.370 --> 09:41.288
LET'S GO.

09:48.671 --> 09:50.338
WHAT I'M
TELLING YOU IS

09:50.506 --> 09:51.631
YOU DRAW
POWDERMAN'S PAY,

09:51.799 --> 09:54.175
YOU LOAD AND BLAST
THE WAY I TELL YOU.

09:54.343 --> 09:56.469
[SPEAKING CHINESE]

09:59.307 --> 10:00.557
NOW, YOU TALK
ENGLISH!

10:00.725 --> 10:02.851
YOU KNOW I DON'T
SAVVY THAT LINGO.

10:03.019 --> 10:04.853
I JUST SAID,

10:05.021 --> 10:09.482
I WILL NOT KILL MY CREW
BECAUSE YOU WILL NOT
LISTEN TO REASON.

10:09.650 --> 10:11.818
IT'S NOT YOUR CREW,
CHINA BOY.

10:11.986 --> 10:13.153
YOU WORK FOR ME.

10:13.321 --> 10:15.155
EVERY LAST ONE
OF YOU.

10:15.323 --> 10:17.073
YOU GET
THAT STRAIGHT.

10:17.241 --> 10:20.660
Wing: MR. HARRIS,
WE WORK FOR YOU...

10:20.828 --> 10:25.248
BUT I WILL NOT RISK
THE LIVES OF MY MEN.

10:25.416 --> 10:26.750
WING...

10:26.917 --> 10:30.629
I'VE GOT TO PUNCH
A TUNNEL THROUGH
THAT MOUNTAIN.

10:30.796 --> 10:34.841
ONE LITTLE ACCIDENT,
AND YOU'RE TRYING
TO HIDE.

10:35.009 --> 10:37.093
[COACH APPROACHES]

10:42.266 --> 10:43.558
WHAT'S THE HOLDUP,
HARRIS?

10:43.726 --> 10:46.269
WHY AREN'T THESE
MEN WORKING?

10:46.437 --> 10:48.521
WELL, SIR, THERE'S...
NOTHING SERIOUS.

10:48.689 --> 10:50.565
JUST A LITTLE
MISUNDERSTANDING, SIR.

10:50.733 --> 10:53.818
DELAYS COST
THE RAILROAD MONEY.

10:53.986 --> 10:56.112
END OF STEEL
IS WITHIN 9 MILES.

10:56.280 --> 10:58.073
YOU'VE GOT A TUNNEL
TO FINISH.

10:58.240 --> 10:59.616
Harris: YES, SIR.

10:59.784 --> 11:02.369
WE JUST HAD A SMALL
ARGUMENT, SIR.

11:04.205 --> 11:06.539
MY POWDERMAN
DOESN'T WANT TO LOAD
HEAVY ENOUGH

11:06.707 --> 11:08.458
TO MOVE THE PROPER
AMOUNT OF ROCK.

11:08.626 --> 11:10.543
GET ANOTHER POWDERMAN.

11:10.711 --> 11:12.253
Harris: YES, SIR.

11:12.421 --> 11:13.838
Charles: WE'LL DO IT.

11:17.301 --> 11:19.135
WHO ARE YOU?

11:19.303 --> 11:21.054
MY NAME IS INGALLS.
THIS IS MY PARTNER
EDWARDS.

11:21.222 --> 11:23.807
WE'RE BOTH POWDERMEN.
HAVEN'T HAD A CHANCE
TO TALK TO MR. HARRIS YET.

11:23.974 --> 11:25.975
I GUARANTEE
WE'LL MOVE THAT ROCK
FOR YOU.

11:26.143 --> 11:29.813
WELL, THAT SOLVES
YOUR PROBLEM.
HIRE THEM.

11:29.980 --> 11:32.148
AND REMEMBER,
END OF STEEL
IS COMING AT YOU

11:32.316 --> 11:33.733
LIKE A RUNAWAY
LOCOMOTIVE.

11:33.901 --> 11:35.318
YES, SIR.

11:35.486 --> 11:38.446
JUST ONE THING.
WE WANT TO GET PAID
BY THE WEEK, NOT BY THE MONTH.

11:38.614 --> 11:40.448
THE RAILROAD ONLY
PAYS ONCE A MONTH.

11:40.616 --> 11:42.867
PAY IT BY THE WEEK
OR WE DON'T WORK.

11:45.871 --> 11:48.707
IF THEY EARN IT,
GIVE IT TO THEM.

11:48.874 --> 11:53.169
MIGHT EVEN SWEETEN IT
WITH A LITTLE
HAZARD PAY.

11:53.337 --> 11:54.504
THE MAIN THING IS,

11:54.672 --> 11:56.506
GET IT DONE.

11:56.674 --> 11:58.425
Harris: YES, SIR.

12:06.016 --> 12:07.851
YOU TALK
REAL BIG.

12:08.018 --> 12:11.855
YOU GOT FRANKLIN
THINKING YOU KNOW
HOW TO HANDLE POWDER.

12:12.022 --> 12:14.733
BUT YOU'VE STILL
GOT TO SHOW ME.

12:14.900 --> 12:16.025
AND WE'LL SHOW YOU.

12:16.193 --> 12:18.737
WITH DYNAMITE
OR BLASTING OIL.
EITHER ONE.

12:18.904 --> 12:21.239
WE'LL SEE.

12:24.994 --> 12:27.120
NOW LISTEN, EVERYBODY.

12:27.288 --> 12:28.621
TILL I TELL YOU
DIFFERENT,

12:28.789 --> 12:31.708
THESE TWO FELLAS
ARE YOUR NEW POWDERMEN.

12:31.876 --> 12:34.669
AND WING, YOU RUN
YOUR CREW OF CHINA BOYS,

12:34.837 --> 12:36.588
AND THAT'S ALL YOU DO.

12:36.756 --> 12:38.923
TAKE THEM INTO
THE TUNNEL AND FINISH
THE CLEANUP,

12:39.091 --> 12:41.134
STARTING NOW.

12:41.302 --> 12:43.553
NO.
NOT IF THEY USE

12:43.721 --> 12:46.890
THE SAME HEAVY LOADS
OF EXPLOSIVES
THAT YOU SUGGEST.

12:47.057 --> 12:49.642
I WILL NOT ENDANGER
THE LIVES OF MY MEN.

12:51.228 --> 12:53.104
I'LL GIVE YOU
5 MINUTES.

12:54.857 --> 12:58.401
THEN YOUR PAY STOPS,
AND SO DOES YOUR CHOW.

12:58.569 --> 13:01.446
EITHER WORK OR WALK.
IT'S THAT SIMPLE.

13:03.073 --> 13:04.824
YOU FELLAS,
COME ON.

13:04.992 --> 13:07.619
I'LL SEE IF YOU'RE
AS GOOD AS YOU SAY
YOU ARE.

13:09.789 --> 13:13.875
WE DO NOT WORK,
WE HAVE NO MONEY
TO SEND HOME.

13:14.043 --> 13:17.086
OUR FAMILIES
BACK HOME HAVE
NOTHING TO EAT.

13:17.254 --> 13:19.297
[SPEAKING
CHINESE]

13:27.556 --> 13:29.766
HURRY UP WITH
THAT FUSE.

13:30.935 --> 13:32.644
I'M HURRYING,
I'M HURRYING.

13:35.731 --> 13:38.066
AIN'T YOU PUTTING
AN AWFUL LOT IN THERE?

13:38.234 --> 13:39.567
I'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN IT'S TOO MUCH.

13:39.735 --> 13:41.402
JUST GIVE ME THE ONE
WITH THE FUSE.

13:49.829 --> 13:52.705
I'M WILLING TO SEND
THE WHOLE FACE OF THIS
THING COME OFF.

13:56.794 --> 13:59.254
DON'T JUST LOOK
AT ME. GET ANOTHER
ONE GOING.

14:07.638 --> 14:10.598
BLOOEY.

14:19.775 --> 14:20.900
HOW YOU
DOING?

14:21.068 --> 14:22.318
ALL RIGHT.

14:22.486 --> 14:24.320
LET'S GET
THIS LAST HOLE
LOADED.

14:30.160 --> 14:32.662
ALL RIGHT.
YOU'VE GOT THE JOB.

14:32.830 --> 14:34.289
YOU GET TO MOVING
TWICE AS FAST
AS YOU ARE,

14:34.456 --> 14:35.874
YOU MIGHT JUST STAY
ON THE PAYROLL.

14:36.041 --> 14:37.333
WE CAN MOVE
AS FAST AS
YOU WANT.

14:37.501 --> 14:40.253
AFTER YOU FINISH
LOADING,

14:40.421 --> 14:43.006
YOU CAN GET READY
TO BLOW OFF
THE ENTIRE FACE.

14:43.173 --> 14:45.550
GET SOME MEN
DOWN HERE, GET RID
OF THIS PLATFORM.

14:45.718 --> 14:47.385
COMING RIGHT UP.

14:50.764 --> 14:54.601
WING, WE NEED 6 MEN
TO HANDLE THE SCAFFOLDING.

14:54.768 --> 14:57.145
[MUFFLED ORDERS]

14:57.313 --> 14:58.855
GIVE ME
THAT HOT ONE.

15:01.150 --> 15:02.400
WE GOT THE JOB.

15:02.568 --> 15:05.194
YOU GOT IT.
I GOT A CHANCE TO GET
MY HEAD BLOWN OFF.

15:05.362 --> 15:06.529
DON'T YOU WORRY
ABOUT IT.

15:06.697 --> 15:08.364
YOU JUST STICK
WITH ME.

15:08.532 --> 15:10.700
[CHUCKLES]
YEAH...

15:23.589 --> 15:28.801
FIRE IN THE HOLE!

15:36.602 --> 15:37.810
COME ON, MOVE!

15:37.978 --> 15:39.771
LET'S GO! OUT!

15:53.702 --> 15:55.787
[EXPLOSION]

16:45.629 --> 16:47.714
IT'S NOT
[INDISTINCT],
DEARIE.

16:47.881 --> 16:51.300
THEY PAY NO DIFFERENT
IF YOU LEAVE YOURSELF
TIME TO BREATHE.

16:51.468 --> 16:53.553
NO, IT FEELS GOOD
TO BE DOING SOMETHING,

16:53.721 --> 16:55.096
OTHER THAN JUST
SITTING AROUND.

16:55.264 --> 16:58.641
WELL, NURSE JOHNSON
SAID YOU CAN DO
[INDISTINCT].

16:58.809 --> 17:01.853
AND A BIT OF LAYING DOWN,
TOO, FOR THAT MATTER.

17:02.021 --> 17:04.897
SHE'S PUT A COT
IN THE NURSES'
QUARTERS FOR YOU.

17:05.065 --> 17:06.149
CAN YOU DO THAT?

17:06.316 --> 17:08.609
OH,
WE MOTHERS CAN.

17:08.777 --> 17:13.906
THERE'S NO POINT IN PAYING
FOR AN OUTRAGEOUS
HOTEL ROOM YOU CAN'T USE.

17:14.074 --> 17:18.327
WELL, OFF WITH
YOU NOW. YOUR
SHIFT'S FINISHED.

17:18.495 --> 17:20.121
GO SEE YOUR
LITTLE GIRL.

17:20.289 --> 17:21.873
YOU'RE TOO KIND,
SARAH.

17:22.041 --> 17:23.916
I'LL JUST FINISH
THIS PIECE.

17:24.084 --> 17:25.752
RIGHT.
[CHUCKLES]

17:36.096 --> 17:38.306
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
GOING TO TAKE IT
EASY FOR A WHILE.

17:38.474 --> 17:40.183
WELL, FIGURED
I'D STAY AHEAD
OF THE DRILLERS,

17:40.350 --> 17:42.977
GET THIS DONE WHILE
I WORK THE CLEANUP.

17:48.942 --> 17:51.694
I HAVE
SOMETHING TO SHOW
THE POWDERMEN.

17:52.821 --> 17:54.447
I'VE GOT DRILLS
TO SHARPEN.

17:54.615 --> 17:56.741
OVER THERE.

17:56.909 --> 17:59.243
IT'LL ONLY TAKE
A MINUTE.

18:14.468 --> 18:16.719
MY FAULT.

18:16.887 --> 18:19.806
ROCK FROM
THE TUNNEL ROOF
FELL DOWN,

18:19.973 --> 18:21.766
DAY BEFORE
YOU CAME.

18:21.934 --> 18:24.519
I LOAD THE HOLES
THE WAY YOU LOAD THEM.

18:24.686 --> 18:27.855
THE BLAST BROUGHT
THE ROCK DOWN.

18:28.816 --> 18:30.900
HE NEEDS A DOCTOR.

18:31.068 --> 18:34.904
DOCTOR CAN MEND
BROKEN ARM,
BROKEN LEG.

18:35.072 --> 18:38.074
BUT THIS MAN
IS BROKEN INSIDE.

18:40.953 --> 18:43.955
NOBODY
CAN FIX THAT.

18:44.123 --> 18:46.624
I'M SORRY.
THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO.

18:51.588 --> 18:55.341
I'VE GOT
A DAUGHTER LYING
IN A HOSPITAL BED.

18:55.509 --> 18:59.011
MAYBE THE DOCTORS
CAN HELP HER,
AND MAYBE THEY CAN'T.

18:59.179 --> 19:01.556
BUT WHAT I'M TELLING
YOU IS THAT WE TAKE
CARE OF OUR OWN.

19:01.723 --> 19:03.808
THAT'S THE WAY
IT IS.

19:06.019 --> 19:07.854
Harris: INGALLS...

19:08.021 --> 19:11.065
I'D LIKE TO
SEE YOU TWO MEN
UP AT THE OFFICE.

19:11.233 --> 19:13.484
I HAVEN'T GOT YOU
IN THE PAYBOOK YET.

19:26.498 --> 19:30.376
FIGURED YOU'D HAD ABOUT
ENOUGH OF THE CHINA
BOYS FOR ONE DAY.

19:30.544 --> 19:31.836
YEAH.

19:32.004 --> 19:34.964
HEARD YOU SAY
YOU HAD A DAUGHTER
IN THE HOSPITAL.

19:35.132 --> 19:37.800
I'VE BEEN DOWN
THAT ROAD MYSELF.

19:37.968 --> 19:41.220
HAZARD PAY IS
ABOUT 1/3 MORE THAN
THE REGULAR RATE.

19:41.388 --> 19:42.555
SHOULD BE A HELP.

19:42.723 --> 19:44.599
IT WILL,
THANKS.

19:44.766 --> 19:46.142
TELL YOU WHAT WOULD BE
EVEN A BIGGER HELP,

19:46.310 --> 19:48.519
IF I COULD TELEGRAPH
THAT MONEY TO ROCHESTER
SOMEHOW.

19:48.687 --> 19:50.771
YOU CAN.
I CAN FIX IT.

19:50.939 --> 19:52.315
I APPRECIATE IT.

19:52.482 --> 19:56.110
YOU JUST FOLLOW ORDERS,
KEEP ON DOING WHAT
YOU'RE DOING,

19:56.278 --> 19:57.695
I'LL TREAT YOU RIGHT.

19:57.863 --> 19:59.405
THANK YOU, SIR.

20:01.992 --> 20:03.201
YOU THINK
WING'S RIGHT?

20:03.368 --> 20:05.369
YOU THINK WE'RE
LOADING TOO HEAVY?

20:07.331 --> 20:09.582
IF I'VE GOT A CHOICE,
I GO WITH THE MAN
WHO PAYS ME.

20:18.217 --> 20:20.343
"MY DEAREST MARY,

20:20.510 --> 20:23.012
"HOW I WISH
I COULD BE WITH YOU
RIGHT NOW

20:23.180 --> 20:28.142
"INSTEAD OF HAVING
TO PUT WORDS TO
PAPER SO FAR AWAY.

20:28.310 --> 20:30.519
"I LOVE YOU,
MY DARLING.

20:30.687 --> 20:33.940
YOU'RE IN MY THOUGHTS
AND PRAYERS CONSTANT--"

20:36.526 --> 20:37.860
MARY, I'LL PUT
THIS AWAY.

20:38.028 --> 20:39.362
[FOLDS UP PAPER]

20:39.529 --> 20:42.740
YOU CAN READ IT
YOURSELF WHEN YOU'RE
FEELING BETTER.

20:42.908 --> 20:45.159
MA...

20:47.371 --> 20:49.330
IF SOMETHING HAPPENS...

20:52.292 --> 20:55.169
IF I'M NOT HERE
WHEN PA COMES...

20:55.337 --> 20:56.754
MARY...

20:58.382 --> 21:00.967
MARY,
LOOK AT ME.

21:04.221 --> 21:06.305
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

21:07.391 --> 21:11.018
I JUST WANT YOU
TO TELL HIM
I LOVE HIM,

21:11.186 --> 21:14.105
- AND I TRIED, BUT--
- MARY!

21:14.273 --> 21:16.649
STOP TALKING
LIKE THAT!

21:16.817 --> 21:19.068
I'M NOT GETTING
ANY BETTER, MA.

21:19.236 --> 21:20.569
I CAN FEEL IT.

21:20.737 --> 21:22.947
MARY, I DON'T CARE
WHAT YOU THINK
YOU FEEL.

21:23.115 --> 21:26.409
THE DOCTOR TELLS ME
YOU'RE DOING FINE.

21:28.578 --> 21:30.705
BUT MA...

21:30.872 --> 21:34.583
JUST IN CASE
SOMETHING HAPPENS...

21:34.751 --> 21:36.919
I WANT YOU TO TELL PA
I LOVE HIM--

21:37.087 --> 21:38.379
IF YOU WANT TO TELL
YOUR PA SOMETHING,

21:38.547 --> 21:40.548
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
TO TELL HIM YOURSELF.

21:40.716 --> 21:42.091
AND TO DO THAT
YOU'RE GOING TO

21:42.259 --> 21:45.386
HAVE TO STOP FEELING
SORRY FOR YOURSELF,
AND GET WELL.

21:54.271 --> 21:56.439
I GUESS I DID
SOUND THAT WAY.

21:59.234 --> 22:00.776
WELL...

22:04.448 --> 22:06.615
THAT'S NORMAL.

22:06.783 --> 22:09.452
EVERYBODY FEELS
LIKE THAT SOMETIMES.

22:14.207 --> 22:16.250
THAT'S MY GIRL.

22:20.630 --> 22:23.382
WELL, YOU'RE DOING
A LITTLE BETTER.

22:23.550 --> 22:25.468
I'LL BE GLAD
TO SHOW YOU,
MR. FRANKLIN.

22:25.635 --> 22:27.428
NO NEED,
NO NEED.

22:27.596 --> 22:29.221
USING AS MUCH
DYNAMITE
AS YOU ARE,

22:29.389 --> 22:31.682
YOU HAVE TO BE
MOVING A LOT
OF ROCK.

22:31.850 --> 22:33.392
YES, SIR.
WE ARE.

22:33.560 --> 22:36.479
WE'RE GETTING CLOSE
TO 4 FEET A DAY FOR
A SOLID WEEK NOW, SIR.

22:36.646 --> 22:40.358
ADD ANOTHER FOOT A DAY,
AND YOU JUST MIGHT
FINISH ON SCHEDULE.

22:40.525 --> 22:41.984
WE'LL SURE TRY,
SIR.

22:45.989 --> 22:48.157
- MR. INGALLS.
- YES, SIR.

22:48.325 --> 22:49.992
I HAVE
A QUESTION
FOR YOU.

22:50.160 --> 22:51.577
IF WE DOUBLE
YOUR HAZARD PAY,

22:51.745 --> 22:54.747
DO YOU THINK YOU CAN
GET ANOTHER FOOT
OF TUNNEL A DAY?

22:54.915 --> 22:55.956
NO.

22:56.124 --> 22:57.917
YES, SIR,
WE CAN DO IT.
I GUARANTEE IT.

22:58.085 --> 23:00.211
WELL, THERE YOU ARE,
MR. HARRIS,

23:00.379 --> 23:04.256
FROM NOW ON
WE'LL EXPECT
ANOTHER FOOT A DAY.

23:04.424 --> 23:06.050
YES, SIR.

23:07.761 --> 23:09.553
HE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT HE'S ASKING.

23:09.721 --> 23:11.931
WELL, WE CAN DO IT.
I CAN USE
THE EXTRA MONEY.

23:12.099 --> 23:14.350
THOSE LOADS
WE'RE USING NOW IS
RATTLING THE MOUNTAIN.

23:14.518 --> 23:16.185
LET IT RATTLE.

23:37.457 --> 23:39.708
YOU USE
TOO MUCH
DYNAMITE.

23:41.128 --> 23:43.963
WHAT'S IT TO YOU
HOW MUCH
DYNAMITE I USE?

23:44.131 --> 23:47.758
YOU CAN'T BLAST
AN EXTRA FOOT
OF ROCK PER DAY.

23:47.926 --> 23:51.387
WORD GETS AROUND
FAST, DOESN'T IT?

23:51.555 --> 23:54.557
AFTER EVERY BLAST,
CHINA BOY GOES
INTO TUNNEL FIRST.

23:54.724 --> 23:56.934
NOW THE ROOF ROCK
FALLS DOWN,

23:57.102 --> 24:00.146
CHINA BOY GETS HURT,
OR KILLED.

24:01.273 --> 24:02.773
IF THAT'S
ALL THAT'S
BOTHERING YOU,

24:02.941 --> 24:05.151
I'LL BE THE FIRST MAN
IN THE TUNNEL
AFTER EVERY BLAST.

24:05.318 --> 24:07.570
I'LL CHECK THE OVERHEAD,
AND BAR DOWN
ANY LOOSE ROCK.

24:07.737 --> 24:08.821
DOES THAT
SATISFY YOU?

24:08.989 --> 24:13.784
I WILL WAIT AND WATCH,
SEE YOU KILL YOURSELF.

24:15.454 --> 24:17.121
I'VE GOT
WORK TO DO.

24:42.731 --> 24:44.273
[COUGHS]

24:54.618 --> 24:55.993
DAYS AREN'T
LONG ENOUGH.

24:56.161 --> 24:57.786
YOU'VE GOT TO
COME IN HERE IN
THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

24:57.954 --> 25:00.289
AND DO SOMEBODY ELSE'S
WORK. WHAT FOR?

25:00.457 --> 25:02.666
AH, THE DRILLERS ARE
SHORTCHANGING ME.

25:02.834 --> 25:05.586
THEY DON'T WANT ME
TO GET THAT EXTRA
FOOT A DAY.

25:05.754 --> 25:07.004
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
ALL OVER CAMP FOR YOU.

25:07.172 --> 25:10.299
FIGURED
YOU'D BE IN HERE.
A TELEGRAM CAME.

25:27.984 --> 25:29.568
WHAT IS IT, CHARLES?

25:31.655 --> 25:33.656
IT SAYS...

25:35.951 --> 25:37.868
MARY'S GOT
HER STRENGTH BACK.

25:40.080 --> 25:41.997
THEY'RE GOING TO
OPERATE ON HER AGAIN.

25:42.165 --> 25:43.749
Isaiah: IT'S GOING TO
BE ALL RIGHT.

25:43.917 --> 25:46.585
THE THING YOU'VE GOT
TO DO, CHARLES, IS GET
YOURSELF SOME SLEEP.

25:46.753 --> 25:48.879
NO.

25:49.047 --> 25:50.673
[FOLDING PAPER]

25:50.840 --> 25:52.883
I'M FINE.

25:53.051 --> 25:56.554
MY BABY'S GOING TO GET
THE BEST CARE, AND...

25:56.721 --> 25:59.348
IT'S GOING TO
TAKE MONEY.

25:59.516 --> 26:00.641
CHARLES.

26:00.809 --> 26:02.768
I SAID
I'LL BE FINE.

26:04.854 --> 26:07.064
[HAMMERING]

26:29.629 --> 26:38.304
[SPEAKING CHINESE]

26:41.391 --> 26:43.559
[MAN SPEAKING CHINESE]

27:04.623 --> 27:07.082
Harris: HEY, WAIT.
WHAT'S GOING ON
AROUND HERE?

27:07.250 --> 27:08.417
IT'S NOT
QUITTING TIME.

27:08.585 --> 27:11.045
WE GO TO HONOR
AND BURY OUR FRIEND
LIN CHOU,

27:11.212 --> 27:13.297
WHO IS DEAD BECAUSE
I WAS A FOOL!

27:32.025 --> 27:33.442
YOU'D BETTER
GET THOSE
LANTERNS FILLED.

27:33.610 --> 27:34.693
WE'VE GOT
WORK TO DO.

27:34.861 --> 27:36.612
FUNERAL GOING ON,
CHARLES.

27:36.780 --> 27:38.781
SOMEBODY
I DON'T KNOW,
AND I CAN'T HELP.

27:38.948 --> 27:41.825
IT AIN'T VERY CHRISTIAN
TO BE BLASTING
IN THE MIDDLE OF IT.

27:43.620 --> 27:45.788
NOW, I'M GOING TO GET
THAT EXTRA FOOT A DAY.

27:45.955 --> 27:47.873
I WANT THE MONEY.

27:48.041 --> 27:50.209
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
YOU CAN'T
SPARE AN HOUR?

27:50.377 --> 27:51.960
WHAT'S HAPPENED
TO YOU, CHARLES?

27:52.128 --> 27:55.339
WHY DON'T YOU GIVE ME
A SERMON LATER, AND JUST
FILL THE LANTERNS?

28:01.930 --> 28:04.223
I'VE HAD
ENOUGH OF YOU
AND THAT TUNNEL.

28:04.391 --> 28:06.100
NOW, I'M GOING
TO THAT FUNERAL,

28:06.267 --> 28:09.561
AND WHEN I'M DONE,
I'M GOING TO PACK MY STUFF
AND GET OUT OF HERE.

28:16.236 --> 28:17.861
WELL...

28:18.029 --> 28:20.823
WHAT WAS
ALL THAT ABOUT?

28:20.990 --> 28:23.617
JUST A DIFFERENCE
OF OPINION.

28:23.785 --> 28:25.703
I'VE GOT TO GET
BACK AT IT.

28:38.675 --> 28:41.427
[SPEAKING
CHINESE]

28:54.441 --> 28:57.776
[SPEAKING CHINESE]

29:04.951 --> 29:06.493
BETTER TO MOVE
SOME ROCK.

29:06.661 --> 29:08.787
LET ME GET STARTED,
I'LL LOAD HER UP.

29:24.554 --> 29:26.388
[SPEAKING CHINESE]

29:43.323 --> 29:45.991
Man: [SPEAKING CHINESE]

29:56.586 --> 29:58.837
[EXPLOSION]

30:25.406 --> 30:27.074
HEY...
[LAUGHS]

30:27.242 --> 30:29.034
THAT'S NOT BAD,
IT'S NOT BAD.

30:29.202 --> 30:32.955
YEAH, WE'RE NOT GOING TO HAVE
ANY TROUBLE MAKING
THAT EXTRA FOOT A DAY, HUH?

30:33.122 --> 30:35.457
[RUMBLING]

30:38.253 --> 30:39.419
DO YOU HEAR
SOMETHING?

30:39.587 --> 30:41.547
[RUMBLING]

30:43.800 --> 30:45.300
HEY, RUN!
CAVE-IN!

30:45.468 --> 30:47.553
[RUMBLING]

31:29.804 --> 31:31.388
COME ON, WE'VE GOT--
WE'VE GOT TWO MEN
TRAPPED IN THERE.

31:31.556 --> 31:32.806
WE'VE GOT TO GET
THEM OUT OF THERE!

31:32.974 --> 31:36.351
WE NEED TOOLS,
TORCHES, AND MORE
ROCK CARTS.

31:36.519 --> 31:38.186
WELL, COME ON,
MOVE!

31:40.899 --> 31:43.358
YOU TELL THEM,
GET IN THE TUNNEL.

31:43.526 --> 31:45.569
TELL THEM TO GET
IN THE TUNNEL!

31:47.196 --> 31:49.531
MOVE! GET IN THERE!

31:49.699 --> 31:51.617
GET IN THERE!

31:52.535 --> 31:53.577
MY FRIEND IS TRAPPED
IN THERE.

31:53.745 --> 31:54.995
YOU'RE GOING TO
HELP ME GET HIM OUT!

31:55.163 --> 31:57.873
NOW GET
IN THE TUNNEL!

31:58.041 --> 32:00.709
YOU BUNCH OF COWARDS!

32:00.877 --> 32:04.713
YOU!

32:04.881 --> 32:06.715
ALL RIGHT, MAYBE
YOU DON'T LIKE THEM,

32:06.883 --> 32:10.177
BUT YOU JUST CAN'T
STAND HERE AND WATCH
THEM DIE IN THERE!

32:11.971 --> 32:14.556
ALL RIGHT, MAYBE
THEY ASKED FOR IT...

32:14.724 --> 32:16.308
LOOK...

32:16.476 --> 32:18.852
MY BEST FRIEND IS
IN THERE. I CAN'T
GET HIM OUT BY MYSELF.

32:19.020 --> 32:21.480
I NEED YOUR HELP!

32:24.108 --> 32:25.609
WING.

32:25.777 --> 32:28.528
YOU'RE THE ONE MAN
I THOUGHT WOULD
GIVE ME A HAND.

32:28.696 --> 32:29.821
I MEAN,
OF ALL THE MEN
ON THIS JOB,

32:29.989 --> 32:31.740
I THOUGHT YOU'D
GIVE ME A HAND!

32:41.459 --> 32:42.584
Charles: HERE...

32:42.752 --> 32:44.836
THAT'S A LITTLE
BETTER.

32:45.004 --> 32:46.964
[COUGHS]

32:49.175 --> 32:50.759
- THERE YOU GO.
- OHH...

32:50.927 --> 32:53.261
IT'S YOUR LEG?

32:53.429 --> 32:55.889
HOW BAD DO YOU
THINK IT IS?

32:56.057 --> 32:58.850
IT'S BRUISED,

32:59.018 --> 33:01.061
BUT NOT BROKEN.

33:03.731 --> 33:05.399
OKAY, JUST
SIT STILL.

33:05.566 --> 33:07.526
I'LL SEE
IF I CAN GET US
OUT OF HERE.

33:21.708 --> 33:25.210
IT'S PLUGGED UP
TIGHT AND SOLID.

33:28.089 --> 33:30.257
[COUGHS]

33:43.646 --> 33:45.522
THE BLAST RIPPED
INTO THE FAULT.

33:47.817 --> 33:51.069
YOUR POUNDING WILL
BRING IT ALL DOWN.

33:53.823 --> 33:56.992
I CAN LET THEM
KNOW WE'RE ALIVE.

33:57.160 --> 33:59.995
IT WON'T MAKE
ANY DIFFERENCE.

34:00.163 --> 34:04.750
NOT A MAN OUT THERE
WOULD RISK HIS LIFE
TO GET US OUT.

34:07.170 --> 34:12.632
THEY'LL GET US OUT.

34:21.017 --> 34:23.727
[VOICES APPROACHING]

34:27.857 --> 34:31.109
WE'VE ALREADY BURIED
ONE MAN TODAY.

34:31.277 --> 34:32.819
THAT'S ENOUGH.

35:05.269 --> 35:07.938
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

35:12.777 --> 35:15.445
YOU'RE WASTING
YOUR TIME.

35:19.075 --> 35:21.451
I'VE GOT NOTHING
ELSE TO DO.

35:32.171 --> 35:34.339
I DID A LOT OF LYING
TO YOU TO GET THIS JOB.

35:34.507 --> 35:35.841
[COUGHS]

35:37.635 --> 35:39.886
I NEVER WORKED IN
A TUNNEL BEFORE.

35:42.974 --> 35:45.642
WELL...

35:45.810 --> 35:48.895
YOU NEEDED THE MONEY
FOR YOUR DAUGHTER.

35:50.648 --> 35:54.484
I DON'T HAVE ANY EXCUSE.

35:54.652 --> 35:56.486
I WAS JUST...

35:56.654 --> 35:59.531
AFRAID OF BEING FIRED.

35:59.699 --> 36:02.701
THEY THINK
I'M TOO OLD.

36:03.911 --> 36:04.911
AHH...

36:05.079 --> 36:07.539
THEY SEND OUT
A YOUNG KNOW-NOTHING

36:07.707 --> 36:10.917
TO PUSH AND CROWD.

36:12.295 --> 36:15.338
TILL THEY CAN FIND
A REASON TO FIRE ME.

36:20.386 --> 36:24.222
I'VE GOT ENOUGH LAID BY
TO TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

36:24.390 --> 36:28.518
IT'S NOT THAT.

36:28.686 --> 36:33.231
IT'S JUST HAVING NOTHING
TO DO THAT HURTS.

36:33.399 --> 36:36.568
I SPENT
A LOT OF YEARS...

36:38.487 --> 36:40.822
DRILLED
A LOT OF TUNNELS,

36:40.990 --> 36:43.116
LEARNING
MY TRADE.

36:44.744 --> 36:48.163
AND I'M BETTER NOW
THAN I EVER WAS.

36:50.791 --> 36:53.376
BUT WHEN A MAN'S
BEING CROWDED,

36:53.544 --> 36:57.088
HE MAKES MISTAKES.

36:57.256 --> 36:59.341
AND I MADE A BEAUTY.

37:02.345 --> 37:03.470
HARRIS,
WE BOTH DID.

37:03.638 --> 37:05.263
[ROCKS TUMBLING]

37:11.270 --> 37:13.188
BETTER CHECK
YOUR LANTERN.

37:13.356 --> 37:16.983
WE'RE RUNNING
OUT OF AIR.

37:37.088 --> 37:39.881
Mary: [MOANING]

37:42.385 --> 37:48.098
MA?

38:00.278 --> 38:02.195
SEND SOMEONE
FOR DR. WASHBURN,
GET ME AN ORDERLY,

38:02.363 --> 38:03.613
AND SEE THAT
THE SURGERY
IS READY.

38:03.781 --> 38:05.282
YES,
DR. MAYES.

38:07.576 --> 38:08.785
YOU'RE GOING TO
OPERATE?

38:08.953 --> 38:10.287
I'D HOPED THAT
SHE'D BE STRONGER,

38:10.454 --> 38:14.165
BUT WE CAN'T WAIT,
NOT NOW.

38:24.176 --> 38:25.719
CLAMP, PLEASE.

38:29.598 --> 38:32.434
Dr. Mayes:
HOW'S SHE DOING?

38:32.601 --> 38:35.103
HER PULSE
IS TOO WEAK.

38:35.271 --> 38:37.939
HOLD ON, MARY.

38:38.107 --> 38:40.608
HOLD ON.

38:40.776 --> 38:43.570
IT'S JUST
A LITTLE WHILE LONGER.

38:43.738 --> 38:45.822
SPONGE.

38:47.199 --> 38:50.035
[THUNDER]

38:51.954 --> 38:53.330
LIGATURE.

39:13.059 --> 39:14.809
MRS. INGALLS?

39:17.563 --> 39:19.522
MARY IS BACK
IN HER ROOM.

39:19.690 --> 39:22.025
ALL THE SIGNS
ARE GOOD.

39:25.071 --> 39:27.197
THANK YOU.

39:37.541 --> 39:39.834
[WHISPERING]
FATHER...

39:40.002 --> 39:43.546
WHO ART
IN HEAVEN...

39:43.714 --> 39:47.050
HALLOWED BE
THY NAME.

39:47.218 --> 39:49.844
THY KINGDOM
COME...

39:50.012 --> 39:52.680
THY WILL BE
DONE...

39:52.848 --> 39:54.766
ON EARTH...

39:54.934 --> 39:57.143
AS IT IS IN HEAVEN.

39:58.479 --> 40:00.313
DEAR GOD...

40:03.192 --> 40:05.610
GOD, TAKE CARE
OF MY BABY.

40:08.572 --> 40:10.990
TAKE CARE OF MY BABY.

40:14.036 --> 40:16.121
PLEASE, GOD.

40:18.874 --> 40:20.417
AMEN.

40:30.052 --> 40:31.803
Nurse: MRS. INGALLS.

40:37.726 --> 40:40.145
MA...

40:46.235 --> 40:48.736
YOU'RE
A FIGHTER,
HONEY.

40:50.906 --> 40:53.241
JUST LIKE
YOUR PA.

41:15.055 --> 41:17.140
[PANTING]

41:27.234 --> 41:29.360
[PEBBLES FALLING]

41:33.073 --> 41:35.158
[THUMPING]

41:46.378 --> 41:48.421
[PEBBLES FALLING]

42:14.490 --> 42:17.700
CHARLES!

42:20.246 --> 42:23.373
[LAUGHS]

42:25.042 --> 42:27.919
[LAUGHING]
EDWARDS!

42:31.799 --> 42:42.517
[LAUGHING]

43:10.212 --> 43:12.338
WHAT IS
THE HOLDUP NOW?

43:12.506 --> 43:15.425
HARRIS!

43:15.593 --> 43:17.385
WHY AREN'T THESE
MEN WORKING?

43:22.808 --> 43:25.143
YOU WERE SAYING,
MR. FRANKLIN?

43:28.147 --> 43:29.731
YOU'RE FIRED!

43:29.898 --> 43:32.191
I DON'T NEED YOU.

43:33.777 --> 43:36.904
WING COULD DO THE JOB
AS GOOD AS YOU
EVER COULD.

43:37.072 --> 43:40.742
WING, YOU'RE
IN CHARGE NOW.

43:43.787 --> 43:45.538
GET THIS CREW TO WORK!

43:45.706 --> 43:49.292
[SPEAKING CHINESE]

43:53.505 --> 43:56.049
GET YOUR CREW
TO WORK!

43:56.216 --> 43:58.384
IF YOU FIRE
MR. HARRIS,

43:58.552 --> 44:01.095
WE QUIT.

44:01.263 --> 44:02.347
SO DO I.

44:02.514 --> 44:04.057
AND ME.

44:08.395 --> 44:10.730
AND WHILE YOU'RE
STANDING THERE WITH
YOUR MOUTH OPEN,

44:10.898 --> 44:13.775
THERE'S
A COUPLE OF THINGS
I WANT YOU TO KNOW.

44:13.942 --> 44:16.194
FIRST, YOU'VE GOT
A BUSTED-DOWN TUNNEL,

44:16.362 --> 44:19.947
AND SECOND,
THERE'S GOING TO BE
BRASS JUMPING OVER BRASS

44:20.115 --> 44:22.533
TRYING TO PIN
THE BLAME ON SOMEBODY,

44:22.701 --> 44:24.619
AND IT AIN'T
GOING TO BE
ANY OF US,

44:24.787 --> 44:26.496
BECAUSE NONE OF US
ARE GOING TO BE HERE.

44:26.664 --> 44:31.084
THERE'S ONLY GOING TO BE
ONE PERSON LEFT HERE
HOLDING THE BAG,

44:31.251 --> 44:32.585
AND THAT'S YOU!

44:32.753 --> 44:34.212
AND WHEN THEY GET
THROUGH WITH YOU,

44:34.380 --> 44:36.464
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO
BE ABLE TO GET A JOB

44:36.632 --> 44:39.759
ANYWHERE ON ANY RAILROAD
AT ANY TIME!

44:40.803 --> 44:43.179
AND IF YOU DON'T
KNOW THAT ALREADY,

44:43.347 --> 44:46.349
I'M HAPPY
TO BE THE MAN
TO TELL YOU FIRST.

44:48.018 --> 44:50.186
- HOWEVER...
- WAIT...

44:50.354 --> 44:54.065
IF YOU WANT TO SPEAK
KINDLY TO MR. WING...

44:54.233 --> 44:56.484
OR MR. INGALLS...

44:56.652 --> 44:58.861
OR MR. EDWARDS...

44:59.029 --> 45:01.906
THEN THEY MIGHT
JUST TIDY UP YOUR
LITTLE MESS FOR YOU,

45:02.074 --> 45:04.909
SO THAT NO ONE
WOULD BE
ANY THE WISER.

45:05.077 --> 45:06.994
BUT AT THEIR OWN
GOOD TIME,

45:07.162 --> 45:09.789
AND WITH NOBODY
GETTING HURT.

45:09.957 --> 45:12.333
THE CHOICE
IS UP TO YOU.

45:17.840 --> 45:20.174
MR. HARRIS,

45:20.342 --> 45:22.510
JUST GET
THE JOB DONE.

45:26.432 --> 45:28.099
WING...

45:28.267 --> 45:31.185
START THE CLEANUP.

45:31.353 --> 45:33.438
MR. WING.

45:40.863 --> 45:42.989
[CHATTER]

45:48.620 --> 45:50.371
[TRAIN BELL RINGS]

46:00.090 --> 46:02.216
[BRAKES HISS]

46:17.441 --> 46:18.900
MA'AM...

46:19.067 --> 46:21.486
LET ME HAVE
A BUNCH OF THOSE
FLOWERS.

46:21.653 --> 46:23.112
THANK YOU.

46:50.224 --> 46:51.307
- NURSE?
- YES?

46:51.475 --> 46:52.475
WHERE'S MARY?

46:52.643 --> 46:53.726
IT'S ALL RIGHT,
MR. INGALLS.

46:53.894 --> 46:55.937
YOUR WIFE TOOK HER
OUT TO THE GARDEN.

46:56.104 --> 46:58.105
- THANK YOU.
- YOU'RE WELCOME.

47:05.614 --> 47:08.324
Caroline:
...LAY DOWN
OR SOMETHING?
